This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for improving the discriminative power of deep generative models. It also involves the development of an efficient algorithm for optimization. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep generative models are a popular area of research in AI. 

The paper uses MNIST and SVHN datasets, which are image datasets, indicating that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves the development of a new algorithm for optimization, which could also place it in the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
